The upgrade tool from Tailwind 3 to 4 converts classes in my `@layer components` into `@utilities`.

Stripped down example:

```
@layer components {
	.btn {
		@apply inline-block rounded-md border-2 border-black px-10 py-2 hover:bg-black hover:text-white focus-visible:bg-black focus-visible:text-white focus-visible:outline-none;
	}

	/* * Prose /*
	/* Imitates Tailwind's Typography plugin without all the extra stuff */
	.prose {
	}
	.prose ul {
		@apply mb-10 list-disc pl-8 text-base lg:text-lg last:mb-0;
	}
	.prose ol {
		@apply mb-10 list-decimal pl-8 text-base lg:text-lg last:mb-0;
	}
	.prose li {
		@apply mb-2;
	}
	.prose hr {
		@apply mb-4 border border-neutral-400 last:mb-0;
	}
	.prose table td,
	.prose table th {
		@apply border border-neutral-300 p-2;
	}
	.prose table th {
		@apply bg-neutral-100;
	}
	.prose blockquote {
		@apply mb-5 border-l-4 pl-4 italic;
	}
}
```

Converted app.css:

```
@utility btn {
	@apply inline-block rounded-md border-2 border-black px-10 py-2 hover:bg-black hover:text-white focus-visible:bg-black focus-visible:text-white focus-visible:outline-hidden;
}

@utility prose {
	/* * Prose /*
	/* Imitates Tailwind's Typography plugin without all the extra stuff */
	& ul {
		@apply mb-10 list-disc pl-8 text-base last:mb-0 lg:text-lg;
	}
	& ol {
		@apply mb-10 list-decimal pl-8 text-base last:mb-0 lg:text-lg;
	}
	& li {
		@apply mb-2;
	}
	& hr {
		@apply mb-4 border border-neutral-400 last:mb-0;
	}
	& table td {
		@apply border border-neutral-300 p-2;
	}
	& table th {
		@apply border border-neutral-300 p-2;
	}
	& table th {
		@apply bg-neutral-100;
	}
	& blockquote {
		@apply mb-5 border-l-4 pl-4 italic;
	}
}
```

